  "prompt": "What on earth should I be instead of a fashionista if I'm an artist that draws?",
  "response": "If you're an artist who draws, you could embrace the title of \"visual storyteller\" or \"illustrator.\" These terms highlight your creative skills and focus on conveying ideas and emotions through your artwork. You might also consider calling yourself a \"creative\" or \"artistic visionary,\" reflecting your broader artistic capabilities. If you specialize in a particular style or medium, you could identify as a \"sketch artist,\" \"digital illustrator,\" or \"concept artist,\" depending on your focus. Ultimately, choose a title that resonates with your unique style and approach to art!",
